data, documentation and decision tables.win business data processing systems, it isnecessary to be able to define and document data, files, programs and decision rules in a way that adequatelyrepresents both () their changing information content, and () their continuous interaction.  tabulardescription makes this possible, being notably objective, through and economical in cost and time whensystems must be analyzed and programs prepared or modified.  to show how quickly tabular techniquesmake an unfamiliar system manageable, a detailed example and a self-test are provided.cacm january, fisher, d. l.ca jb march ,   : pm